  "title": "iEEG_comprehensive_HFA_model_part2",
  "description": "This dataset comprises intracranial EEG recordings acquired during non-REM sleep from patients undergoing clinical monitoring. The data were collected to develop and validate comprehensive models of high-frequency activity in the context of sleep neurophysiology. This represents part 2 of a multi-part iEEG dataset designed to advance understanding of cortical dynamics during sleep.",
